references + open notes

references. recordings. mixes. links. writings. etc.

LE CINEMA CLUB

Now showing... Here's a list of films that I watched for the first time on this site and admired. The numbers mean nothing. There is no best or worst.

  1. MOUNE Ô by MAXIME JEAN-BAPTISTE
  2. THE SLOW BUSINESS OF GOING by ATHINA RACHEL TSANGARI
  3. ALL DAY I DREAM ABOUT SPORT by GABRIEL MOSES + PHARRELL WILLIAMS

JAZZ RECORD LABELS TO KEEP UP WITH

These include contemporary, modern, classic, underground, and defunct. This list isn't supposed to be all encompassing but I want to add as many as possible so that I remember upcoming releases or past releases I missed. A lot of new things happening! Most of these are Bandcamp links because this is where I go for the most part for new releases.

  1. International Anthem Recording Company
  2. Gondwana Records
  3. Pi Recordings

KENNY GARRETT: BLUE NOTE TOKYO 1991
